Approach
We understood the problem as a knowledge discovery issue inside organizations. Important information exists, but it is difficult to find quickly.
Our user flow starts with a user uploading a document, URL, or Slack thread. The system extracts the content, stores it in a searchable knowledge base, and allows users to ask natural language questions. The assistant then retrieves relevant information and generates an answer with source references.
We decided to build features like document upload, Q&A, summarization, multi-turn chat, auto-tagging, and scoped access. AI is used for summarizing documents, understanding user questions, generating answers, creating tags, and retrieving relevant knowledge. The approach is useful because it works inside Slack, where employees already communicate.You can include:

